==================================================================
TrafficMon 

City Traffic Monitor and Controller using Reinforcement Learning

Supervisor / Mentor: Mike Bain 
Authors: Gautam Manoharan (gman086@cse) and Sean Young (seany@cse)
Date: 3 June 2012

==================================================================

Directories
===========

src: program source files (c++)
doc: report  


Building Prerequisites
======================

FreeGLUT (Linux) or GLUT (Mac OS X)


Building TrafficMon
===================

TrafficMon is tested on Mac OS X and Linux.

On Mac OS X, run:
$ make -C src 

On Linux, run:
$ make -f Makefile_lin -C src


Running TrafficMon
==================

$ bin/TrafficMon


Inside TrafficMon
=================

Some keyboard controls for moving around in the Graphical Display

J: pan camera left
L: pan camera right
K: pan camera down
I: pan camera up
M: mirror keys

T: toggle training / validation

Z: zoom in
X: zoom out

S: step in
SPACE BAR: pause/resume
D: toggle display
R: reset screen

ESC: quit

P: print learned q table to file

-: slow down simulation / learning
+: speed up simulation / learning


Bug Reporting (IMPORTANT!!!)
============================

All bugs should be reported to Gautam Manoharan or Sean Young
